{{orphan|date=July 2011}} {{Infobox magazine | title = Dosheeza Digest | image_file = Dosheeza Digest May 2012 cover.jpg | image_size = 203px | image_alt = | image_caption = May 2012 cover of ''Dosheeza'' | editor = Rashid, Ghazala | editor_title = | previous_editor = | staff_writer = | frequency = [[wikt:Monthly|Monthly]] | circulation = | category = [[Fiction]] [[Women's magazine]] | company = | publisher = | founded = 1982 | firstdate = <!-- {{Start date|year|month|day}} --> | country = [[Pakistan]] | based = [[Karachi]] | language = [[Urdu]] | website = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} --> | issn = }}
'''''Dosheeza''''' is a [[Urdu language]] [[Pakistan]]i family and fictional digest/magazine publish from the [[Karachi]], [[Sindh]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Dosheeza Digest - Monthly|url=http://www.emarkaz.com/shop/store/emarkazBookDetail.php?product_id=3783|work=Emarkaz|accessdate=6 September 2014}}</ref> The magazine was first published in 1982.<ref name=bzu>{{cite journal|title=Women Journalism in Pakistan|journal=Pakistan Journal of Social Sciences|date=December 2009|volume=29|issue=2|url=http://www.bzu.edu.pk/PJSS/vol29no2_2009/FinalPJSS15.pdf|accessdate=11 July 2015}}</ref> It is a monthly digest based on fiction and women's magazine in Urdu language.<ref>[http://dawn.com/2013/01/07/in-the-land-of-films-heroines-and-detectives/ In the land of films, heroines and detectives], Eefa Khalid, ''Dawn Newspaper'', 7 January 2013, Retrieved: 13 January 2013, ''... Over the years I have seen my parents buying Jasoosi Digest, Dosheeza, Khawateen Digest, and Akhbar-e-Jahan, and I always admired the work by those artists ...''</ref> It has its headquarters in Karachi.<ref name=bzu/>
