==Bibliography== {{refbegin|30em }} * {{cite web | url = http://www.illustratedgarden.org/mobot/rarebooks/author.asp?creator=Bauer,%20Ferdinand%20Lukas&creatorID=96 | title = Ferdinand Lukas Bauer | accessdate = 2007-08-17 | author = Hu Walsh | date = 2003-10-23 | work = Rare books | publisher = Missouri Botanical Garden | quote = production costs were excessive so only a limited number of volumes saw the light of day. Yet [[William T. Stearn|Stearn]] (7:34),† ranks Flora Gracea as a masterpiece of printing, engraving, color and design, and notes, "...it is the most costly and beautiful book devoted to any flora." }} († ''see Stearn 1960'') * {{cite book |last= Harris|first= Stephen|title= The Magnificent Flora Graeca; How the Mediterranean Came to the English Garden|year= 2007|isbn= 978-1-85124-306-8}} * {{cite book |author1=Lack, H. W. |author2=Mabberley, David | year = 1998 | title = The Flora Graeca Story: Sibthorp, Bauer, and Hawkins in the Levant | publisher = Oxford University Press | isbn = 0-19-854897-4}} * {{cite journal|last1=Stearn|first1=William T.|authorlink=William T. Stearn|title=Sibthorp, Smith, the 'Flora Graeca' and the 'Florae Graecae Prodromus'|journal=[[Taxon (journal)|Taxon]]|date=1 January 1967|volume=16|issue=3|pages=168–178|doi=10.2307/1216982|jstor=1216982}} * {{cite journal|last1=Stearn|first1=William T.|authorlink=William T. Stearn|title=From Theophrastus and Dioscorides to Sibthorp and Smith: the background and origin of the Flora Graeca|journal=[[Biological Journal of the Linnean Society]]|date=December 1976|volume=8|issue=4|pages=285–298|doi=10.1111/j.1095-8312.1976.tb00251.x|ref={{harvid|Stearn|1976a}}}} * {{cite journal|last1=Stearn|first1=William T.|authorlink=William T. Stearn|title=Franz Bauer and Ferdinand Bauer, masters of botanical illustration|journal=[[Endeavour (journal)|Endeavour]] (First series)|date=1960|volume=19|pages=27–35|ref=harv}}{{refend}}
